1) Install httpd (http daemon)
  # yum -y install httpd

2) Start httpd
  #systemctl start httpd

3) Enable (for reboot)
  #systemctl enable httpd


Configure for installation files on http server
  (-p makes parent directories if they don't exist)

  # mkdir -p /var/www/html/inst
  # cp -a <path-to-iso> /var/www/html/inst
  # chcon -R --reference=/var/www/html /var/www/html/inst

  ^This 'chcon' command applied the default SELinux context from /var/www/html to /var/www/html/inst (-R = recursively)


Configure firewall 

  # firewall-cmd --permanent --add-service=http
  # firewall-cmd --reload


Ensure Apache Web Server is running and Enabled

  # systemctl restart httpd
  # systemctl enable httpd


Mounting DVD/ISO

  # mount /dev/cdrom /media
  # mount -ro loo <path-to-iso> /media
